    "Convolution neural network basic architecture (Buckner,).",
    "Activation layers are critical components that enable CNNs to learn non-linear transformations of complex patterns for object detection tasks.",
    "These layers capture subtle relationships between features, leading to advanced models with enhanced generalization capabilities.",
    "As illustrated in Table 1, popular activation functions include ReLU (Fukushima, 1975), Tanh (Hereman and Malfliet, 2005), Leaky ReLU (Bai, 2022), ELU (Clevert et al., 2015), Sigmoid (Ramachandran et al., 2017), and SELU (Zhu et al., 2023), each with unique characteristics (Nwankpa et al., 2018).",
